{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e8c2be27-1fcd-4c6c-afee-e0f8629893da","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"0.6.1\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This enables `dotnet test` compatibility with MTP.\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` v0.6.x targets xUnit.net v2 (your 2.9.3 is compatible).\n- MTP gives you faster startup, better parallelism, and a simpler architecture (no VSTest host process).\n- You can also pass `--help` to your built test binary to see MTP-specific options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5240d5a5-a2ea-4939-9bb7-530198c1b94d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":356,"requestId":"3413:386D1F:55DACDA:5DF3C60:69F3FA04"},"id":"ae026b77-1d3e-4adf-9339-39d6eb36020a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:41.539Z","parentId":"b5b04b00-2d36-4c7b-bd78-9ffa51084517"}
